01:59.628 --> 02:00.962
Good morning...

02:05.634 --> 02:06.384
I’m Dr. Jung.

02:07.552 --> 02:08.887
I admitted you yesterday.

02:12.265 --> 02:13.183
I’m not...

02:14.226 --> 02:16.645
I’m not mad, you know.

02:20.482 --> 02:22.275
Let me explain what I have in mind.

02:23.652 --> 02:28.698
I propose that we meet here, most
days, to talk for an hour or two.

02:29.783 --> 02:30.617
Talk?

02:31.201 --> 02:32.035
Yes.

02:32.077 --> 02:33.203
Just talk.

02:34.621 --> 02:36.540
See if we can identify
what’s troubling you.

02:37.749 --> 02:42.462
So as to distract you as little as possible,
I’m going to sit there, behind you.

02:42.504 --> 02:47.300
I’m going to ask you to try not to turn around
and look at me under any circumstances.

02:51.471 --> 02:52.347
Now...

03:05.735 --> 03:09.823
Have you any idea what may have brought
on these attacks you suffer from?

03:11.116 --> 03:12.033
Hu...

03:15.954 --> 03:17.998
humiliation.

03:22.836 --> 03:25.129
Any kind of...

03:25.130 --> 03:28.258
humiliation.

03:28.300 --> 03:33.305
Like, I can’t bear to see it and
it makes me feel nauseated.

03:33.346 --> 03:38.101
I start pouring with sweat, cold sweat.

03:39.728 --> 03:40.310
My...

03:40.311 --> 03:40.896
my...

03:43.523 --> 03:52.407
my father lost his temper all the time.
He was always angry with me.

03:57.787 --> 04:02.542
When you stopped talking just now,
did a thought come into your head?

04:04.878 --> 04:05.545
I...

04:05.546 --> 04:06.880
I don’t know...

04:06.922 --> 04:09.090
Or an image, perhaps.

04:10.217 --> 04:11.051
Was it an image?

04:11.092 --> 04:12.344
Yes.

04:14.095 --> 04:15.013
What was the image?

04:16.723 --> 04:19.351
It was a hand.

04:19.392 --> 04:19.935
My...

04:19.976 --> 04:20.435
my...

04:20.476 --> 04:24.022
my father’s hand.

04:24.064 --> 04:25.815
Why do you think you saw that?

04:29.277 --> 04:31.029
Whenever he would...

04:33.949 --> 04:34.699
after...

04:34.741 --> 04:35.534
whenever he...

04:39.371 --> 04:42.332
he hit us, afterward we...

04:42.374 --> 04:45.877
we had to kiss his hand.

04:49.548 --> 04:55.679
What’s odd is that case I was writing up last
week, I happened to pick the codename Sabina S.

04:55.720 --> 04:58.931
And here she is... Sabina Spielrein.

04:58.932 --> 05:00.725
Quite a coincidence.

05:02.018 --> 05:04.145
As you know, I don’t believe
there is such a thing.

05:06.606 --> 05:08.775
Spielrein’s not a very Russian name.

05:09.776 --> 05:11.194
No, Jewish.

05:11.236 --> 05:14.948
Father’s a very successful
import-export man.

05:14.990 --> 05:18.910
And she’s exceptionally well
educated, speaks fluent German.

05:18.952 --> 05:21.788
Aspires to be a doctor herself, apparently.

05:22.706 --> 05:23.832
Perhaps she’s the one.

05:25.333 --> 05:26.042
What one?

05:26.084 --> 05:27.793
The one you’ve been looking for.

05:27.794 --> 05:29.838
For your experimental treatment.

05:29.880 --> 05:31.173
The talking cure.

05:33.633 --> 05:34.885
You’re so astute.

05:34.926 --> 05:37.804
I’ve already begun it with her.

05:39.723 --> 05:40.557
He’s kicking.

05:40.599 --> 05:42.100
Can you feel?

05:44.853 --> 05:45.687
Oh, yes.

05:45.729 --> 05:47.063
There he is.

05:49.774 --> 05:53.268
What I don’t understand is
why Freud, having proposed

05:53.269 --> 05:56.827
this radical therapeutic idea,
this talking cure, this

05:56.828 --> 06:00.257
psychoanalysis, then lets
years go by without giving

06:00.258 --> 06:03.622
even the barest outline of
his clinical procedures?

06:03.663 --> 06:04.956
What’s he playing at?

06:04.998 --> 06:07.667
Presumably he uses the
method on his patients?

06:07.709 --> 06:09.419
I’ve no idea.

06:10.587 --> 06:12.964
So might you be the first
doctor to try this out?

06:13.006 --> 06:14.049
It’s possible.

06:15.133 --> 06:16.676
Why don’t you write and ask him?

06:17.552 --> 06:18.512
I don’t know him.

06:20.847 --> 06:25.352
As it happens, Miss Spielrein’s mother
wanted to take her to see Freud.

06:27.437 --> 06:29.064
Another coincidence.

06:31.733 --> 06:34.194
My father thinks my
mother doesn’t love him.

06:35.320 --> 06:36.655
And he’s right, she doesn’t.

06:37.614 --> 06:38.490
How do you know?

06:40.700 --> 06:42.160
My angel told me.

06:43.745 --> 06:44.579
What angel?

06:46.331 --> 06:47.958
An inner voice.

06:47.999 --> 06:51.461
He used to tell me I was
an exceptional person.

06:51.503 --> 06:53.922
For some reason he always spoke in German.

06:53.964 --> 06:57.676
Angels always speak German
... It’s traditional.

06:57.717 --> 07:02.430
He gave me the power to know what people are
going to say before they open their mouths.

07:03.682 --> 07:05.308
Useful ability for a doctor.

07:05.350 --> 07:08.520
You hope to be a doctor
some day, don’t you?

07:10.564 --> 07:11.690
I’ll never be a doctor.

07:11.731 --> 07:12.983
Why not?

07:24.286 --> 07:25.620
I have to go away for awhile.

07:25.662 --> 07:27.497
I’m sorry.

07:27.539 --> 07:28.540
We’ve just gotten started.

07:29.666 --> 07:30.792
Military service.

07:30.834 --> 07:32.251
We all have to do it.

07:32.252 --> 07:34.004
Just for a couple of weeks.

07:34.045 --> 07:34.713
It’s a waste of time!

07:34.754 --> 07:38.258
I can’t tell you whatever
it is you want to know!

07:38.300 --> 07:39.009
You’re just...

07:39.050 --> 07:40.010
you’re just making me angry.

07:40.051 --> 07:41.928
And even if I could tell you,
you’d be sorry you ever...!

07:43.889 --> 07:46.683
Anyway, there’s nothing wrong with me!

07:46.725 --> 07:47.893
I don’t even want to get better!

07:51.021 --> 07:52.063
Stop it!

07:53.398 --> 07:54.065
What?

07:54.107 --> 07:56.276
Will you just stop that!

07:59.529 --> 08:00.363
I’m sorry.

08:04.784 --> 08:06.077
Can we get back now?

08:06.119 --> 08:07.537
Yes, if you want to.

08:07.579 --> 08:08.622
I need to get back.

08:10.957 --> 08:12.876
It’s a complete waste of my time.

08:16.213 --> 08:20.592
Writing prescriptions for athlete’s foot and
examining cocks from morning ‘til night.

08:21.718 --> 08:23.053
Is that what you do?

08:23.094 --> 08:25.222
It’s not good for me.

08:25.263 --> 08:27.224
It’s not good for my patients.

08:47.410 --> 08:48.578
You’re playing with your food.

08:48.579 --> 08:50.455
I'm not hungry.

08:51.831 --> 08:52.916
Is that so?

08:56.962 --> 08:58.797
I shall have to tell Professor Bleuler.

08:58.839 --> 09:00.173
Ha.

09:02.259 --> 09:03.176
Do what you like.

09:23.488 --> 09:25.865
Please, Miss, give me your hand.

09:25.866 --> 09:26.741
Please.

09:26.783 --> 09:29.578
You’ll catch your death.

09:30.203 --> 09:31.162
Miss Spielrein.

09:35.208 --> 09:36.543
The Herr Direktor.

09:38.712 --> 09:41.131
Blueleri feel you may have a little
too much time on your hands.

09:41.173 --> 09:45.010
I’m a great believer in getting our
patients involved in some productive work.

09:45.051 --> 09:47.053
What are your particular interests?

09:49.097 --> 09:50.015
Suicide.

09:50.056 --> 09:52.559
Interplanetary travel.

09:52.601 --> 09:54.769
When Dr.

09:54.811 --> 09:58.398
Jung returns, I shall ask him to discuss
all this with you in more detail.

09:59.400 --> 10:00.776
You keep him away from me.

10:00.818 --> 10:02.820
I never want to see him again!

10:12.538 --> 10:13.956
Now, come along.

10:13.997 --> 10:15.165
Don’t make such a fuss.

10:17.251 --> 10:18.460
Give me those legs.

10:27.177 --> 10:28.345
Here’s the sponge?

10:28.346 --> 10:30.014
Just lie still.

10:30.055 --> 10:32.391
That’s better.

10:37.187 --> 10:37.855
